<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>swear on a stack of Bibles • swear on the Bible</xh5><p> <i>swear on a stack of Bibles—</i>promise solemnly that what one says is true: Your telephone company will <u>swear on a stack of Bibles</u> that nothing will disrupt service to you, the valued customer.</p><p> <i>swear on the Bible—</i>1. place one’s hand on the Bible in a court of law pledging to tell the truth: A court officer will ask you to <u>swear on the Bible</u> or promise to tell the truth. 2. <i>= swear on a stack of Bibles: </i>There are probably a lot of people that think I’m lying, and I <u>swear on the Bible</u> that this story is true.</p> </entry>
